text.tspan: 2. The agency has a policy for capital program prioritisation

flowRoot.flowPara: Intent: To identify the extent to which the agency has a Board/Executive team approved policy in place for capital program prioritisation. The policy should be consistent with other agency policies, refers to the key outcomes or objectives to be achieved through capital program prioritisation, outline the approach to prioritisation, and provide sufficient flexibility in unusual circumstances.

text.tspan: 2014 Q1 » 1. Corporate Policy and Business Planning

flowRoot.flowPara: The Corporate Policy and Business Planning function includes enablers and controls for undertaking asset management within the agency, as well as the asset management plans and capital programs. This function includes the 'line of sight activities' from business objectives through to the preparation of asset management plans required to meet those business objectives.

The Asset Management System comprises the agency asset management policy, asset management objectives, asset management strategy, asset management plans, and the activities, processes and organisational structures necessary for their development, imlementation and continual improvement.

The Asset Management System is often confused with Asset Management Information Systems. The Asset Management System encompasses the processes, procedures, governance, review and continual improvement processes that surround the entire set of tools and organisational enablers that help the organisation manage its assets.
